And it has a lower
y-intercept.

00:06:41.110 --> 00:06:42.820
And we want all the
values below it or

00:06:42.820 --> 00:06:43.800
equal to that line.

00:06:43.800 --> 00:06:46.540
So all of these values
over here.

00:06:46.540 --> 00:06:50.280
Now, the area that overlaps
between these two constraints,

00:06:50.280 --> 00:06:53.260
I'll do it in this yellow color,
is below the blue line,

00:06:53.260 --> 00:06:56.220
including the blue line, and
above the red line, including

00:06:56.220 --> 00:06:56.800
the red light.

00:06:56.800 --> 00:06:58.760
So it's this area right here.

00:07:03.050 --> 00:07:10.770
So any combination of games
and music that are in that

00:07:10.770 --> 00:07:15.010
area will meet both of
his constraints.

00:07:15.010 --> 00:07:17.160
And one thing you might want to
consider, since you can't

00:07:17.160 --> 00:07:22.090
buy half a game or half a song,
it would only be kind of

00:07:22.090 --> 00:07:25.630
the integer coordinates in this
region that would satisfy

00:07:25.630 --> 00:07:26.490
his constraints.

00:07:26.490 --> 00:07:32.230
So however many games, however
many songs this is and music

00:07:32.230 --> 00:07:35.250
is, this would satisfy
his constraints.

